# Docker MCP (MCP_DOCKER)

For **Docker and container** tasks, use the **`MCP_DOCKER`** MCP server (Docker MCP Gateway) â€” not ad-hoc shell guesses when MCP tools are available.

## When to use MCP_DOCKER

- `docker compose up`, `down`, `ps`, logs, build errors
- Diagnosing failed image builds (`failed to solve`, missing `COPY` paths)
- Container health, ports, volumes, networking
- Finding and enabling Docker-related MCP servers via `mcp-find` / `mcp-add`

Prefer MCP over raw `docker` in the shell when the gateway exposes the needed tool. If a tool is missing, use `mcp-find` (query: `docker`, `compose`, `container`) and `mcp-add` before falling back to shell.

## When NOT to use MCP_DOCKER

- Editing **source code** in the repo â€” file tools
- **pytest**, **git**, codebase search â€” **`atlas-grid-dev`** ([atlas-grid-dev-mcp.mdc](atlas-grid-dev-mcp.mdc))
- Live app data (projects, jobs) â€” **`atlas-grid`** ([atlas-grid-mcp.mdc](atlas-grid-mcp.mdc))

## Setup

- Configured in **user** Cursor MCP: `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\mcp.json` â†’ server `MCP_DOCKER`
- Command: `docker mcp gateway run --profile profile`
- Requires **Docker Desktop** running on Windows
- Cursor â†’ **Settings â†’ Tools & MCP** â†’ enable `MCP_DOCKER` for Agent â†’ **Reload**
- If MCP is unavailable in the session: use shell (`docker compose`, `docker ps`, `docker logs`) and say that MCP was not attached

## Local backend image (`deploy/docker-compose.dev.yml`)

Before first `docker compose` build, stage vendor copies (same as CI `deploy-yandex-vm.yml`):

```powershell
.\scripts\stage-backend-vendors.ps1
```

Or manually:

```powershell
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force decision-matrix\shared decision-matrix\backend\shared
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force autoroad-network-planner decision-matrix\backend\network-planner-vendor
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force pad-earthwork-planner decision-matrix\backend\pad-earthwork-vendor
Copy-Item -Recurse -Force well-trajectory-planner decision-matrix\backend\well-trajectory-vendor
```

Vendor directories are **gitignored** â€” do not commit them; re-run staging after microservice changes before `--build`.

Then from repo root: `docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.dev.yml up --build` (first time / after Dockerfile or vendor changes). Daily start: `up` or `up -d` without `--build`.

